race.comment: MOGO MAGIC (1) bolted in over this distance at the Kensington track two back. Tackled the rich Barn Dance over 1300m at Randwick last start and folded late after racing handy. Will be tough to stop this evening back in his right grade. BALKANS (7) loomed up on the corner but didn't have the change of gears required when third last time out over 1100m here. Generally races well at Canterbury and the step up in distance is a plus. Worth another chance. ROLLING MAGIC (5) ran into one dead end after another then sprouted wings when clear only to just miss in a desperately unlucky return over 1300m at Rosehill recently. Up a little in grade but with that run under the belt he looks a serious contender. THE GREAT HOUDINI (4) had a 45-day break before his modest effort at Randwick last start. Strips fitter and can improve. ISTOLEA MERC (6) has disappointed as favourite at his last two but he gets out to his preferred distance now so he can improve without surprising.
